In ''[[NetHack]]'', the '''apostrophe''' ('''<nowiki>'</nowiki>''') serves the following purposes:

* {{white|'}} represents a [[golem]]:
** {{monsymlink|straw golem}}
** {{monsymlink|paper golem}}
** {{monsymlink|rope golem}}
** {{monsymlink|gold golem}}
** {{monsymlink|leather golem}}
** {{monsymlink|wood golem}}
** {{monsymlink|flesh golem}}
** {{monsymlink|clay golem}}
** {{monsymlink|stone golem}}
** {{monsymlink|glass golem}}
** {{monsymlink|iron golem}}

==Historical uses==
In Hack 1.21, which is based on of [[Jay Fenlason's Hack]], the [[ghost]] uses the {{white|'}} glyph; in Hack for PDP-11, the glyph is given to the [[lurker above]]. [[Hack 1.0]] moves the lurker above to the [[tilde]] glyph, {{white|~}}, and [[Hack 1.0.1]] moves it back to {{white|'}}, where it remains from this version to [[NetHack 2.3e]].

In [[NetHack 3.0.0]], the golems are introduced and given the {{white|'}} glyph, and the lurker above is moved to the {{white|t}} glyph with the [[trapper]].

